history.content: Hi, I'm not sure if this is the correct place to ask this. I was wondering if someone could redirect me to someone I could contact about this. It seems like the servers in Cory are down, so we are not able to use any software that requires a licensing server (for example HSPICE). We are not able to print in the labs as well. The printing isn't really a problem for us but we really need to be able to use HSPICE for our lab, and I heard that this server problem is affecting other classes as well. Is there anyone we can contact to check if this is an acknowledged issue?
history.subject: Cory servers are down?
